ORIGINAL: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
ENGLISH: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
CZECH: Demoliční nálož, tvořená hlavně z dynamitu či silnějších exploziv.
GERMAN: Eine Rucksackladung ist eine Abbruchvorrichtung, die hauptsächlich für den Kampf bestimmt ist und deren Hauptbestandteile eine Ladung Dynamit oder ein stärkerer Sprengstoff wie ein C4-Kunststoffsprengstoff, eine Tragevorrichtung, die einer Rucksack- oder Umhängetasche funktionell ähnlich ist, und ein Auslösemechanismus sind. Der Begriff umfasst sowohl improvisierte als auch formal gestaltete Geräte.
RUSSIAN: Военное взрывное устройство, основным компонентом которого является динамит или более мощное вещество, такое как C4 - переносное устройство с взрывным механизмом, внешне похожее на ранец или сумку. Этот термин охватывает как импровизированные так и формально изготовленные устройства.
POLISH: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
HUNGARIAN: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
ITALIAN: Una Carica Satchel è un dispositivo di demolizione, primariamente utilizzato per i combattimenti, i cui componenti principali sono una carica di Dinamite (o esplosivi più forti, come il C4 al Plastico), un dispositivo di trasporto funzionalmente simile ad una sacchetta o zainetto, ed un innesco. Il termine indica sia quelli improvvisati che quelli prodotti in serie.
SPANISH: Una carga de mochila es un dispositivo de demolición, principalmente destinado al combate, cuyos componentes principales son una carga de dinamita o un explosivo más potente como el explosivo plástico C4, un dispositivo de transporte funcionalmente similar a una mochila o bolsa de mensajero, y un mecanismo de disparo; el término cubre dispositivos improvisados ​​y diseñados formalmente.
FRENCH: Une charge en sacoche est un dispositif de démolition, principalement destiné au combat, dont les principaux composants sont une charge de dynamite ou un explosif plus puissant tel qu'un explosif plastique C4, un dispositif de transport fonctionnellement similaire à une sacoche ou un sac de messager, et un mécanisme de déclenchement; le terme couvre à la fois les dispositifs improvisés et formellement conçus.
CHINESE: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
PORTUGUESE: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
JAPANESE: A satchel charge is a demolition device, primarily intended for combat, whose primary components are a charge of dynamite or a more potent explosive such as C4 plastic explosive, a carrying device functionally similar to a satchel or messenger bag, and a triggering mechanism; the term covers both improvised and formally designed devices.
CHINESESIMP: 挎包炸药是一种主要用于战斗的拆卸装置，其主要成分是炸药或更强力的炸药，例如C4塑料炸药，功能类似于挎包或信使袋的运载工具以及触发装置； 该术语涵盖简易设备和正式设计的设备。
